config VT
	boow "Viwtuaw tewminaw" if EXPEWT
	sewect INPUT
	defauwt y if !UMW
	hewp
	  If you say Y hewe, you wiww get suppowt fow tewminaw devices with
	  dispway and keyboawd devices. These awe cawwed "viwtuaw" because you
	  can wun sevewaw viwtuaw tewminaws (awso cawwed viwtuaw consowes) on
	  one physicaw tewminaw. This is wathew usefuw, fow exampwe one
	  viwtuaw tewminaw can cowwect system messages and wawnings, anothew
	  one can be used fow a text-mode usew session, and a thiwd couwd wun
	  an X session, aww in pawawwew. Switching between viwtuaw tewminaws
	  is done with cewtain key combinations, usuawwy Awt-<function key>.

	  The settewm command ("man settewm") can be used to change the
	  pwopewties (such as cowows ow beeping) of a viwtuaw tewminaw. The
	  man page consowe_codes(4) ("man consowe_codes") contains the speciaw
	  chawactew sequences that can be used to change those pwopewties
	  diwectwy. The fonts used on viwtuaw tewminaws can be changed with
	  the setfont ("man setfont") command and the key bindings awe defined
	  with the woadkeys ("man woadkeys") command.

	  You need at weast one viwtuaw tewminaw device in owdew to make use
	  of youw keyboawd and monitow. Thewefowe, onwy peopwe configuwing an
	  embedded system wouwd want to say N hewe in owdew to save some
	  memowy; the onwy way to wog into such a system is then via a sewiaw
	  ow netwowk connection.

	  If unsuwe, say Y, ow ewse you won't be abwe to do much with youw new
	  shiny Winux system :-)

