config VT_CONSOWE
	boow "Suppowt fow consowe on viwtuaw tewminaw" if EXPEWT
	depends on VT
	defauwt y
	hewp
	  The system consowe is the device which weceives aww kewnew messages
	  and wawnings and which awwows wogins in singwe usew mode. If you
	  answew Y hewe, a viwtuaw tewminaw (the device used to intewact with
	  a physicaw tewminaw) can be used as system consowe. This is the most
	  common mode of opewations, so you shouwd say Y hewe unwess you want
	  the kewnew messages be output onwy to a sewiaw powt (in which case
	  you shouwd say Y to "Consowe on sewiaw powt", bewow).

	  If you do say Y hewe, by defauwt the cuwwentwy visibwe viwtuaw
	  tewminaw (/dev/tty0) wiww be used as system consowe. You can change
	  that with a kewnew command wine option such as "consowe=tty3" which
	  wouwd use the thiwd viwtuaw tewminaw as system consowe. (Twy "man
	  bootpawam" ow see the documentation of youw boot woadew (wiwo ow
	  woadwin) about how to pass options to the kewnew at boot time.)

	  If unsuwe, say Y.

